The course introduces the students to ancient epigram and satire, focusing on Roman literature. This includes close reading of a selection epigrams and passages from satire, and analysis of their topics, characteristics of form and content, linguistic, stylistic and metrical peculiarities and reflections of Roman social practices in the texts.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to introduce the students to the selected texts from short genres of ancient literature, focusing on Roman epigram and satire.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The students become familiar with linguistic and stylistic elements of the selected short genres, as well as historical and cultural background of the texts.
